# Quality Gates (kids_math)

> **Canonical source: `AGENTS.md`** — this file provides Cursor-specific details.

> ⚠️ **Tests run on CI, not locally.** The full/long suite (`test:e2e`, `test:qa`) runs
> **only on the PR's CI** — it's faster and costs far fewer tokens. Locally run only the
> fast gates (`tsc`, `lint`, `check:testids`, `test:unit`). "READY" = fast gates pass +
> PR CI green; report the CI Suite field as `DEFERRED TO CI`. See `AGENTS.md` → Testing
> Strategy → Where tests run.

## Quality Gates by Mode

### PRO
```bash
npm run lint
npm run check:testids
# If behavior changed: npm run build
# If logic changed: npm run test:unit -- <specific-test-file>
```

### ULTRA
```bash
npm run lint
npm run check:testids
npm run build
npm run test:unit
# MCP Playwright visual check (if ANY UI changed)
# test:e2e / test:qa → PR's CI, NOT locally. Push and confirm CI is green before READY.
```

### MAX
```bash
npx tsc --noEmit && npm run lint && npm run check:testids && npm run test:unit
# MCP Playwright visual check (ALWAYS — all changed screens)
# test:e2e / test:qa → PR's CI, NOT locally. PR CI must be green before READY.
```

## Mandatory Test Targeting (specific, not "targeted")

| Changed Area | Must Run |
|-------------|----------|
| UI copy/layout | `tests/e2e/day-smoke.spec.ts` |
| Routing/gates/middleware | `tests/e2e/grade-b.spec.ts tests/e2e/grade-a-lifecycle.spec.ts tests/e2e/admin-progress.spec.ts` |
| Progress/storage | `tests/unit/lib/progress/` AND `tests/e2e/grade-a-lifecycle.spec.ts` |
| Final exam | `tests/unit/lib/final-exam/` AND `tests/e2e/grade-a-lifecycle.spec.ts tests/e2e/grade-b-lifecycle.spec.ts` |
| Content/days | `tests/unit/lib/content/content-validity.test.ts` AND `tests/e2e/day-smoke.spec.ts` |
| GMAT | `tests/unit/lib/gmat-challenge/` AND `tests/e2e/gmat-challenge.spec.ts` |

**Storage / schema / content IDs:** Changes that affect persisted progress (including renaming `dayId` or section/exercise ids) must follow **`AGENTS.md` → Data & Storage Rules** and run the applicable rows in the table above.

## Security Gate (mandatory, all modes)

```
SECURITY GATE
[ ] No hardcoded secrets (grep: API_KEY, SECRET, TOKEN, PASSWORD, sk-, pk_)
[ ] No console.log in production code (non-test .ts/.tsx)
[ ] No sensitive data in data-testid values
[ ] No unvalidated user input reaching storage or DOM
[ ] Cookie operations use proper flags
[ ] API route handlers validate inputs
[ ] No TODO/FIXME/HACK in security-critical code

Result: [PASS / FAIL — findings with severity]
```

If CRITICAL finding → auto-BLOCK, STOP, fix immediately.
If HIGH finding → BLOCK merge, must fix.

## Verification Report (ULTRA/MAX mandatory, PRO recommended)

```
VERIFICATION REPORT (kids_math)
================================
Mode:        [PRO/ULTRA/MAX]
Changed:     [description]

Lint:        [PASS/FAIL]
TestIDs:     [PASS/FAIL]
Build:       [PASS/FAIL/SKIPPED — reason]
Unit:        [PASS/FAIL/SKIPPED — reason] (X passed, Y failed)
E2E:         [DEFERRED TO CI — runs on PR pipeline, not locally]
Security:    [PASS/FAIL] (findings with severity)
Visual:      [PASS/FAIL/SKIPPED — reason] (screens checked: list)
CI Suite:    [DEFERRED TO CI / GREEN — PR run link] (local fast gates: lint ✓, testids ✓, unit X/X ✓)
Diff:        [X files, Y insertions, Z deletions]

Self-Review: [CLEAN / X issues caught and fixed]
Learning:    [YES — summary / NO — reason]

Overall:     [READY / NOT READY]
```

### READY Decision Tree

READY if ALL true:
- Zero CRITICAL issues
- Zero HIGH issues
- All gates PASS (or SKIPPED with valid reason)
- Security gate PASS
- Visual verification PASS (or SKIPPED with valid reason)
- CI Suite green on the **PR's CI** (ULTRA/MAX) — not run locally; local fast gates (tsc/lint/testids/unit) pass
- Report 100% filled (no blanks)
- Self-review completed
- Learning updated (ULTRA/MAX) or justified skip

NOT READY if ANY: CRITICAL, HIGH, gate FAIL, report incomplete.

**SKIPPED must have reason:** `SKIPPED [PRO, only copy changed]` not just `SKIPPED`.

## Review Severity Levels

| Level | Meaning | Action | Auto-block? |
|-------|---------|--------|------------|
| **CRITICAL** | Security vuln, data loss, broken gate | BLOCK, no exceptions | YES |
| **HIGH** | Bug, test failure, type error, broken flow | BLOCK before merge | YES |
| **MEDIUM** | Warning, missing test, a11y concern | Should fix | NO |
| **LOW** | Style, suggestion | Optional | NO |

### Security Severity (specific)
| Finding | Severity |
|---------|----------|
| Hardcoded secret / credential | CRITICAL |
| XSS vector | CRITICAL |
| console.log in prod | HIGH |
| Sensitive data in testid/analytics | HIGH |
| Weak validation | MEDIUM |

